      {
        ""name"": ""Joshua Tree Visitor Center"",
        ""parkCode"": ""jotr"",
        ""description"": ""Located in downtown Joshua Tree just five miles from the West Entrance, the Joshua Tree Visitor Center offers educational exhibits, a bookstore, and visitor resources. Grab a park map, buy an entrance pass, and chat with a park ranger to get all your questions answered before heading into the park! The parking lot at the visitor center has 2 standard accessible spaces and 40 other spaces. The restrooms have grab bars available in all larger stalls intended for wheelchair users and running water."",
        ""url"": ""http://www.nps.gov/jotr/planyourvisit/visitorcenters.htm"",
        ""directionsInfo"": ""From CA Hwy 62 (the Twentynine Palms Highway) in downtown Joshua Tree, turn south onto Park Blvd. The Joshua Tree Visitor Center will be on your right."",
